---
title: One-Pan Santa Fe Pork Tacos with Monterey Jack & Cilantro Lemon Slaw
description: We firmly believe taco night should be treated like a holiday—one that should be celebrated at LEAST once a week, if not more. If you agree, you’ve got to add this Southwest version to your repertoire. Spiced ground pork and onion are piled into steamy tortillas with Monterey Jack cheese, a tangy cilantro lemon slaw, and sour cream. Taco ’bout a killer meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/621553e7143a35226e03d7f8-46ca880b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-santa-fe-pork-tacos-621553e7143a35226e03d7f8-a3b3a7dd.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 920 kcal
  fat: 56 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 2060 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-santa-fe-pork-tacos-621553e7143a35226e03d7f8
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

While pork cooks, in a large #bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the cilantro, juice from half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use 2 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Stir @Tex-Mex paste{1} into pan with pork mixture until fully coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with pork filling, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, slaw, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.